$ PowerShell module MS-Office: get-msOfficeInstallationRoot
@ get-msOfficeInstallationRoot

The function `get-msOfficeInstallationRoot` of the → Windows/PowerShell/modules/personal/MS-Office[PowerShell module `MS-Office`] returns
the → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/OfficeN/index[root directory] of a → Microsoft/Office[Microsoft Office] installation.
-
This *root directory* stores the → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/EXE[executables] of the
outlook applications
(→ Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/OfficeN/EXCEL_EXE[`EXCEL.EXE`],
 → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/OfficeN/WINWORD_EXE[`WINWORD.EXE`] etc. as well as those of some helper programs such
as → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/OfficeN/SELFCERT_EXE[`SELFCERT.EXE`]).

sa:
  `get-msOfficeInstallationRoot` is used to locate the path of `→ Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/OfficeN/DCF/SPREADSHEETCOMPARE_EXE` in the PowerShell script
  → Windows/dirs/Program-Files/Microsoft-Office/root/OfficeN/DCF/SPREADSHEETCOMPARE_EXE#spreadsheetcompare-ps[`compare-spreadsheets.ps1`].
